"{\"uid\": \"metro.co.uk-2024-10-23-british-olympian-former-worlds-strongest-man-dies-aged-75-21853956\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Three-time Olympian and former world's strongest man Geoff Capes has died at the age of 75, his family have announced.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 118, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 11, \"end\": 19, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999826031318081, \"rank\": 1.739716852783062e-05, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 53, \"end\": 64, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geoff_Capes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Geoff Capes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geoff_Capes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geoff_Capes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Capes is Great Britain's greatest ever shot putter and still holds the record for the longest throw, which he set in 1980 with a distance of 21.68m.\", \"from\": 120, \"to\": 268, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 129, \"end\": 142, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999998176463, \"rank\": 9.666672198626058e-11, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Away from athletics, Capes was crowned the World's Strongest Man on two occasions, first taking the crown in 1983 and becoming a two-time champion two years later.\", \"from\": 270, \"to\": 433, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In a statement, Capes' family said: 'The family of Geoffrey Capes would like to announce his sad passing today, 23rd October.\", \"from\": 435, \"to\": 560, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"'Britain's finest shot putter and twice world's strongest man.'\", \"from\": 562, \"to\": 625, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 563, \"end\": 570, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9696244326296884, \"rank\": 0.03131939674450122, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Lincolnshire-born star represented Great Britain at three Olympic Games but failed to win a medal, his best finish coming at Moscow 1980 when he finished fifth.\", \"from\": 627, \"to\": 791, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 666, \"end\": 679, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999998176463, \"rank\": 9.666672198626058e-11, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 756, \"end\": 767, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1980_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999344627234, \"rank\": 6.553521277776262e-08, \"text\": \"Moscow 1980\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1980_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1980_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But Capes travelled to Russia as a big medal hope so later admitted his performance in Moscow left him 'numbed with disappointment'.\", \"from\": 793, \"to\": 925, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 816, \"end\": 822, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"score\": 0.718568811191872, \"rank\": 0.3484169711640319, \"text\": \"Russia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia_men's_national_ice_hockey_team\"}, {\"begin\": 880, \"end\": 886, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"score\": 0.9999824149865658, \"rank\": 1.7439925235481957e-05, \"text\": \"Moscow\", \"types\": [\"Q3455524\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moscow\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While he went without an Olympic medal, Capes won two Commonwealth golds and two European indoor world titles.\", \"from\": 927, \"to\": 1037, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 981, \"end\": 993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999999943102011, \"rank\": 5.588053365005471e-09, \"text\": \"Commonwealth\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Commonwealth_Games\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Capes was also a six-time world champion at the Highland Games.\", \"from\": 1038, \"to\": 1101, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Capes was a household name and a regular on TV screens in the 1980s - often showing off his incredible strength - and appeared on reality shows following his retirement from competition.\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1289, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"British Athletics said on X: 'We are saddened to hear the news of former British shot putter, Geoff Capes' passing.\", \"from\": 1291, \"to\": 1406, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1291, \"end\": 1298, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.9318535653490428, \"rank\": 0.07233695602829437, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\"}, {\"begin\": 1364, \"end\": 1371, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.9318535653490428, \"rank\": 0.07233695602829437, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\"}, {